    "text": "The crd_client.go implementation follows the established patterns in the Kubernetes client-go codebase for implementing typed clients for custom resources. The implementation references key files from the client-go project:\n\n1. **gentype/type.go** (kubernetes/client-go): This file defines the ClientWithListAndApply generic type and the NewClientWithListAndApply function that provides Create, Get, List, Delete, Update, Patch, and Apply methods. The Widget client uses ClientWithListAndApply[*Widget, *WidgetList, *WidgetApplyConfiguration] to implement the WidgetInterface.\n\n2. **kubernetes/typed/core/v1/configmap.go** and **kubernetes/typed/core/v1/secret.go**: These files demonstrate the standard pattern for implementing typed resource clients in client-go. They show how to embed gentype.ClientWithListAndApply in a private struct, define interfaces, and provide constructor functions.\n\n3. **kubernetes/typed/core/v1/core_client.go**: This file demonstrates the group-level client pattern, showing how to create factory functions (NewForConfig, NewForConfigAndClient, NewForConfigOrDie, New) and how to implement the setConfigDefaults function to configure the GroupVersion, APIPath, and other settings for the specific API group.\n\n4. **rest/client.go**: This file defines the rest.Interface which is the core interface used by all typed clients to communicate with the Kubernetes API server. The Interface provides methods like Get(), Post(), Put(), Delete(), and Patch() for making REST API calls.\n\nThe implementation embeds rest.Interface in WidgetV1Client and uses gentype.ClientWithListAndApply to provide a fully-featured typed client that:\n- Uses context.Context for proper context propagation in all methods (Create, Get, List, Delete)\n- Implements the Create(ctx, widget, opts) method following metav1.CreateOptions pattern\n- Implements the Get(ctx, name, opts) method following metav1.GetOptions pattern\n- Implements the List(ctx, opts) method following metav1.ListOptions pattern\n- Implements the Delete(ctx, name, opts) method following metav1.DeleteOptions pattern\n- Supports the example.com/v1 custom resource group and version\n- Provides factory methods (New, NewForConfig, NewForConfigAndClient, NewForConfigOrDie) consistent with client-go conventions"
}

